# storage/ — Uploaded Files

## Purpose
Persistent file storage for user-uploaded content. Mounted into both php and node-server containers.

## Structure
- storage/products/   Product images uploaded by sellers
- storage/reviews/    Images attached to buyer reviews
- storage/stores/     Store logo images

## Access
- Files served at: /uploads/* → nginx aliases this to /var/www/html/storage/
- Upload endpoint (Node): POST / with multipart/form-data → saves to /app/public/uploads/ (= ./storage/)
- Upload endpoint (PHP): FileService.php saves to ./storage/ via $_FILES
- URL pattern: /uploads/products/filename.jpg, /uploads/stores/logo.png etc.

## Notes
- chmod -R 777 applied at PHP container start (docker-compose command)
- node-server volume: ./storage:/app/public/uploads
- nginx-server volume: ./storage:/var/www/html/storage
- Nginx serves /uploads/* with 1-year immutable cache (Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000)
